# Agent Rules

## WSL Docker Stack
- Always run Docker commands using the WSL stack (e.g. prefixing commands with `wsl`, such as `wsl docker` or `wsl docker compose`).
- Do not run bare `docker` or `docker compose` commands directly in the host PowerShell if Docker is managed via WSL.
- Use the testing stack compose configuration as defined in the README:
  `wsl docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.test.yml up --build -d`

## TypeScript Rebuilds
- Before building or rebuilding the Docker containers (such as running `wsl docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.test.yml up --build -d`), always compile the TypeScript/Vite assets first.
- To do this, run `npm run build:js` in `src/Pulswerk.Dashboard/` so the compiled bundles in `wwwroot/` are updated and can be copied during the Docker build context.

## Browser Tests & Browserless Container
- When performing browser tasks or UI verification, strictly use/point to the local `browserless` Docker container running at `http://localhost:3000` (or `ws://localhost:3000`) instead of launching a local browser on the host.

